HEADWORD: fringepod
<hw>fringepod</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An annual herb having pinnatifid
basal leaves and slender racemes of small white flowers followed by
one-seeded winged silicles.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lacepod.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fringe tree</ent>⟦br⟧
